Harold Nunley (12 January 1912 – June 2005) was an English cricketer.  Nunley was a left-handed batsman who bowled slow left-arm orthodox.  He was born at Raunds, Northamptonshire.
Nunley made three first-class appearances for Northamptonshire in the 1931 County Championship against Glamorgan, Kent and Worcestershire.  In these three matches, he scored a total of just 20 runs at an average of 6.66, with a high score of 12.He died at Kettering, Northamptonshire in June 2005.
